@Max You are more than welcome. The song is intentionally rhymed and musically styled in the canon of Ukrainian traditional lullaby, that is why you can find it healing and an utterly calming. A flying flock of cranes is a symbol of involuntary separation for many Varangian-derived cultures, from the pre-Christian times, and for Ukrainians it is especially true, those birds are sacred in our culture.  It is very strongly resonating with the nation since the ongoing and apparently endless war with Russia produce a lot of separations on a mass scale.
